5.translation:
"Say: I seek refuge in the Lord of daybreak,
from the evil of that which He created,
from the evil of darkness when it settles,
from the evil of the blowers in knots,
and from the evil of an envier when he envies."

3.translation:
"Race toward forgiveness from your Lord and a Garden whose width is like the width of the heavens and earth, prepared for the righteous
Who spend [in the cause of Allah] during ease and hardship and who restrain anger and who pardon the people - and Allah loves the doers of good;
And those who, when they commit an immorality or wrong themselves, remember Allah and seek forgiveness for their sins - and who can forgive sins except Allah? - and [who] do not persist in what they have done while they know."
